 form of Dutch <b>Montfoort</b>, a variant of   Montfort   2 and also a cognate of the French name in 1 above and an altered form of its variant   Montfort   1 (or perhaps vice versa)."]},{"name":"Monforte","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Salvatore, Carmela, Carmine, Rocco, Rosaria, Sal.  Spanish Carlos, Francisco, Luis, Medardo.","Italian and Spanish: habitational name from any of numerous places called Monforte, from Latin <i>mons</i> ‘mountain’ (genitive <i>montis</i>) + <i>fortis</i> ‘strong’, probably a reference to the strategic position of these locations.","English (of Norman origin): variant of   Montfort  . This form of the surname is rare in Britain."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Rotrou I de Montfort sgr de Monfort- le- Retrou was born about 1065. He had at least 1 daughter with Anne de La Porte. He died before 1098."},"et":{"ABT 1065–BEF 1098":"umbes 1065–enne 1098","1070–1102":"1070–1102","1095–Female":"1095–Surnud","1065–1098":"1065–1098","ABT 1065":"umbes 1065","about 1095":"umbes 1095","BEF 1098":"enne 1098","1102":"1102","1098":"1098","1065":"1065","1095":"1095","1070":"1070","Montfort-Sur-Risle,Eure,France":"Montfort-sur-Risle, Eure, Haute-Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"ABT 1065–BEF 1098":"noin 1065–ennen vuotta 1098","1070–1102":"1070–1102","1095–Female":"1095–Kuollut","1065–1098":"1065–1098","ABT 1065":"noin 1065","about 1095":"noin 1095","BEF 1098":"ennen vuotta 1098","1102":"1102","1098":"1098","1065":"1065","1095":"1095","1070":"1070","Montfort-Sur-Risle,Eure,France":"Montfort-sur-Risle, Eure, Haute-Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"ABT 1065–BEF 1098":"environ 1065–avant 1098","1070–1102":"1070–1102","1095–Female":"1095–Décédée","1065–1098":"1065–1098","ABT 1065":"environ 1065","about 1095":"environ 1095","BEF 1098":"avant 1098","1102":"1102","1098":"1098","1065":"1065","1095":"1095","1070":"1070","Montfort-Sur-Risle,Eure,France":"Montfort-sur-Risle, Eure, Haute-Normandie, France","lifeSummary":"Rotrou I de Montfort sgr de Monfor